    Executes a maven goal

    execute_maven.Rd

    Maven goals may be executed with or without a pom.xml file. Some maven goals (e.g. compilation) require the use of a JDK. Goals can be

    execute_maven(
  goal,
  opts = c(),
  pom_path = NULL,
  quiet = .quietly(verbose),
  debug = .debug(verbose),
  verbose = c("normal", "debug", "quiet"),
  require_jdk = FALSE,
  ...
)

    Arguments

    goal

    the goal of the mvn command ( can be multiple ) e.g. c("clean","compile")

    opts

    provided options in the form c("-Doption1=value2","-Doption2=value2")

    pom_path

    optional. the path to a pom.xml file for goals that operate on one

    quiet

    should output from maven be suppressed? (-q flag)

    debug

    should output from maven be verbose? (-X flag)

    verbose

    how much output from maven, one of "normal", "quiet", "debug"

    require_jdk

    does the goal you are executing require a jdk (e.g. compilation)

    ...

    named parameters are passed to maven as options in the form -Dname=value

    Value

    nothing, invisibly
